<HEADLINE>
<P>
BLADES WIN, 11-8, PLAYOFFS AWAIT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In a game filled with fights and penalties, the Los Angeles Blades defeated 
the Las Vegas Flash, 11-8, Sunday in a Roller Hockey International contest at 
the Thomas & Mack Center in Las Vegas. 
</P>
<P>
 Craig Charron had a hat trick and Mike Doers scored two goals for the Blades 
before 4,289. 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles finishes the regular season with the best record in the Pacific 
Division at 18-4. 
</P>
<P>
 The Flash finish their inaugural season at 6-15-1. 
</P>
<P>
 The Blades open the playoffs against the San Diego Barracudas on Wednesday at 
7:30 p.m. 
</P>
