<P>
VIA BORGHESE NEVER HEADED IN WINNING DIANA HANDICAP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Via Borghese led from start in scoring a two-length victory over Blazing Kadie 
in the $138,350 Diana Handicap at Saratoga on Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 Via Borghese, a 5-year-old daughter of Seattle Dancer-Angela Serra who was 
ridden by Jose Santos, covered 1 1/8 miles on the inner turf course in 1:52. 
</P>
<P>
 Blazing Kadie, who started on the outside in the field of seven, pressed the 
pace and finished second. It was another length back to Coronation Cup. 
</P>
<P>
 Via Borghese earned $83,010 for Malcolm E. Parrish and returned $11.80, $6.60 
and $3.80. Blazing Kadie paid $16.60 and $6.00 and Coronation Cup returned 
$5.00. 
