<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOCAL NOTES; MARQUIS SWEEPS JUNIOR DIVING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Kristen Marquis of the Mission Viejo Nadadores won the platform competition at 
the Speedo National Junior Olympic championship Sunday in Rockville, Md. 
</P>
<P>
 The victory completed a sweep for Marquis, who won the one- meter springboard 
Friday and the three-meter springboard Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 Erica Sorgi, also of the Nadadores, was second in all three competitions. The 
pair will compete in the Canadian-American-Mexican championships Aug. 19-21 in 
Mexico City. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 The Tustin Bobby Sox softball team playing in the national tournament for 10- 
and 11-year-olds remained undefeated with an 8-3 victory over host Sparks, Nev. 
</P>
<P>
 Sarah Boardman had a two-run double as Tustin scored four runs in the first 
inning. Sparks scored three runs in the sixth to cut the lead to 5-3, but 
Tustin scored three more runs in the top of the seventh. 
</P>
<P>
 Tustin is one of three undefeated teams in the 24-team tournament, which ends 
Tuesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
