<P>
 Bob Moore has joined AmericanTours International as chief operating officer, a 
new position.Before joining the Los Angeles-based firm, Moore was senior vice 
president of sales for Beverly Hills-based Hilton Hotels Corp. He is also vice 
chairman of the Travel Industry Assn. of America. Before he joined Hilton in 
1986, Moore managed one of Hawaii's largest tour operators. AmericanTours 
International is a leading wholesale tour operator, producing revenue of $150 
million last year while bringing more than 600,000 visitors to the United 
States. The company has 500 employees nationwide. 
