<TEXT>
<P>
 Avalon Resort Vote: The Avalon City Council is scheduled to vote Tuesday on a 
development agreement for a 300-room luxury resort hotel on Descanso Beach that 
would enable a Phoenix-based builder to secure financing for the project. The 
city has already approved the plan for the $100 million resort, which would 
feature restaurants and meeting rooms said Avalon City Manager Robert Clark.The 
resort is designed to attract visitors year-round, especially for conventions. 
It is projected to net $25.9 million a year in revenue by its third year of 
operation, said Rick Williams of The Pointe Group, the Phoenix company that has 
already built about two dozen resorts and hotels in the western United States. 
Clark said the resort "would be a huge benefit to the city, both in terms of 
our tax base and in terms of generating business for the rest of the town," 
which is currently served by much smaller hotels. 
</P>
