<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Home Construction Report: The Commerce Department will release its report on 
July construction activity on Tuesday, and local home builders will be paying 
close attention.Rising interest rates have pushed housing starts across the 
U.S. lower for three straight months, and another decline could shatter 
developers' hopes for a late-summer rebound. Some Southern California builders 
-- including Los Angeles-based Kaufman & Broad Home Corp., the state's largest 
-- have already slashed their sales projections for the year. But what's bad 
news for builders could be good news for buyers: The recent sales slowdown is 
forcing prices down at many housing tracts, which takes some of the sting out 
of rising interest rates. 
</P>
