Security official said. . . . The U.S. Treasury will raise $1.450 billion in 
new cash by selling $16.750 billion of one-year bills on Thursday. . . . 
Atlanta-based Delta Air Lines Inc. said it will furlough 101 pilots in October 
as part of a companywide plan to slash up to 20% of all jobs at the airline. 
Delta has about 8,600 pilots and 447 already on furlough. . . . Russian car 
maker Yelaz (Yelabuga Automobile Factory) is holding very preliminary talks 
with General Motors Corp. about forming a joint venture to make cars in the 
Tatarstan auto factory, about 600 miles southeast of Moscow, GM and Yelaz 
officials said. . . . All Nippon Airways Co. will postpone a planned purchase 
