<TEXT>
<P>
 Ford Exports to Gulf Arab States Rise: Auto exports to Gulf Arab states by 
Ford Motor Co., boycotted by the Arab world until the 1980s, rose by more than 
35% in the first six months of 1994, a company statement said.Ford said it 
shipped 8,412 vehicles to the six countries of the Gulf Cooperation Council in 
the first half, up from 6,135 in the same period the previous year. It did not 
give a value for its exports. The GCC groups Saudi Arabia, the United Arab 
Emirates, Kuwait, Bahrain, Qatar and Oman. 
