<HEADLINE>
<P>
AUTHORITIES SEARCH LAKE PIRU FOR MAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By J. E. MITCHELL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A North Hollywood man may have drowned late Sunday at Lake Piru, authorities 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 On a weekend boating trip at the lake, the man, whose identity was not 
immediately available, apparently decided to go swimming although he apparently 
did not know how. 
</P>
<P>
 "What we understand is that even though he could not swim, he thought he would 
get into the water wearing a life vest," said Mike Mason, a civilian pilot for 
the Ventura County Sheriff's Department aviation bureau. "However, when he got 
in, he started struggling and floundering about." 
</P>
<P>
 Family members aboard their rented boat threw him three life vests but he 
apparently continued to sink. A man aboard the boat dived into the lake to save 
him but apparently could not get to him in time, Mason said. 
</P>
<P>
 A sheriff's helicopter unit and a search-and-rescue dive team spent several 
hours Sunday evening combing the lake. As of 9:15 p.m. he had not been located. 
J. E. MITCHELL 
</P>
