ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: FULLERTON; APPLICANTS SOUGHT FOR CITIZENS PANEL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIMI KO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The city's Community Development Citizens Committee is seeking to fill four 
vacancies. 
</P>
<P>
 Anyone interested on serving on the committee, which provides the City Council 
with recommendations on the development, implementation and evaluation of the 
city's federally funded Community Development Block Grant Program, is asked to 
apply by 5 p.m. Sept. 2. 
</P>
<P>
 The committee consists of a representative of the Chamber of Commerce and two 
representatives each from four geographical areas of the city -- north, 
south-central, southeast and southwest. The four open seats are one each from 
the four areas. 
</P>
<P>
 Applicants must either live or work in the area they wish to represent. 
</P>
<P>
 For an application, visit City Hall or call (714) 738-6311. MIMI KO 
