</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two teen-agers were wounded by gunshots late Saturday night as they stood 
outside a fast-food restaurant known as a popular hangout for youngsters, 
police said Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 Agripino Reynaldo Abat Jr., 19, of La Mirada and Roseller Alverado, 18, of 
Garden Grove were shot about 10:40 p.m. at a Taco Bell at 7878 Valley View 
Ave., Sgt. Phil Dascenzi said. 
</P>
<P>
 The two young men were driven to a nearby residence and police were called, he 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 Abat was taken to La Palma Intercommunity Hospital and Alverado was taken by 
helicopter to Mission Hospital Regional Medical Center in Mission Viejo. Their 
injuries were not considered life-threatening, Dascenzi said. 
</P>
<P>
 Details of the shooting were sketchy. Dascenzi said police had not yet 
determined whether the incident was gang-related. 
</P>
<P>
 "There were tons of witnesses and nobody knows who did what," Dascenzi said. 
"We don't know who were suspects and who were onlookers." 
</P>
<P>
 He described the fast-food restaurant as a hangout for teen-agers and said 
much of the crowd dispersed after the shooting. 
</P>
<P>
 No suspects had been identified and police were continuing their 
investigation. 
</P>
