<P>
NATION IN BRIEF; ARIZONA; BIOSPHERE IN SCIENCE PACT WITH COLUMBIA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The troubled Biosphere program is forming a partnership with Columbia 
University to select and execute scientific experiments in the high-tech 
glass-domed enclosure in Oracle, Ariz., officials for both said. A scientific 
team with officials from Biosphere 2 and Columbia University's Lamont-Doherty 
Earth Observatory will jointly review and select research proposals for the 
three-acre complex 35 miles northeast of Tucson. "Our new focus at Biosphere 2 
is to give complete access to the world's scientists investigating the 
