<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAN DIES AFTER TRAFFIC COLLISION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEANNETTE REGALADO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 45-year-old man was killed after he drove through a Woodland Hills 
intersection and struck another car, police said Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 Boruei Chen of Studio City ran a red light at De Soto Avenue and Oxnard Street 
on Saturday morning and hit Elvira Ortega's car as she attempted a left turn, 
said Sgt. Glen Wiggins of LAPD's Valley Traffic Division. Chen's car then 
continued on and hit a light pole, he said. 
</P>
<P>
 Chen died at Kaiser Permanente Hospital an hour later, a coroner's spokesman 
said. Ortega sustained minor injuries. JEANNETTE REGALADO 
</P>
